properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 5 at 9:53PM MST until January 6 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HEAVY MOUNTAIN SNOW POSSIBLE TONIGHT THROUGH LATE MONDAY
EVENING...

* WHAT...Mainly blow snow. Some light snow possible with additional
snow accumulations of up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as
75 mph.

* WHERE...The northern Snowy Mountain Range, including Elk
Mountain and Arlington.

* WHEN...From 5 PM this afternoon to 6 PM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility to around one half mile at
times with snow drifts on area roadways.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM MST MONDAY
